                "__typename": "MediaImage"
              },
              "species": {
                "id": "e54bf48b-d564-5d47-9f01-78b2d8ba7eaa",
                "description": "House sparrows have long been our companions, living alongside us since the Stone Age and are still found in places where humans live. They are social birds that roost in groups and engage in social singing, meaning multiple birds will call together from bushes, like a little sparrow choir. Cleanliness is important and you will frequently see them taking dust baths!",
                "name": "Northern Cardinal",
